Study_Name: Statewide freshwater aquatic plant (macrophyte) monitoring data from 1994 to present
Study_Purpose: Identify aquatic plants, evaluate plant community structure, and note the existence or extent of invasive non-native aquatic plants in freshwater throughout Washington State.  The program is supported by the Freshwater Aquatic Weed Account
Study_QA_Project_Plan_Description:
describes the on-going aquatic plant monitoring program, its objectives and how the objectives are achieved 
https://fortress.wa.gov/ecy/publications/publications/1103106.pdf
Study_QA_Assessment_Level: Level 3 - Data Verified and ASSESSED FOR USABILITY
Study_Result_Description: Results are aquatic plant species names and a subjective distribution value for each waterbody visited
Study_Comment: This is an on-going monitoring program. Note that waterbodies are not sampled randomly.
